# Team Collaboration

This project uses a **shared markdown workspace** for Product, UX, Engineering, and QA agents.

## Start of every session

1. Read `docs/TEAM_WORKSPACE.md` — especially **Active Work** and **Team Log**.
2. If a feature is active, open its spec in `docs/features/<name>.md`.
3. Respect role boundaries: PM (scope/AC), UX (§4 Design), Dev (§5 Engineering), QA (§8 Test plan).

## End of every session (if you changed scope, design, or code)

1. Add a **Team Log** row in `docs/TEAM_WORKSPACE.md` (newest first).
2. Update the feature spec section you own.
3. Record material decisions in the feature spec §6 or workspace **Decision log**.

## New features

- Specs live in `docs/features/` using `_TEMPLATE.md`.
- Follow `docs/features/README.md` for status workflow.
- Do not start implementation until acceptance criteria (§3) exist and status is at least `Review`.

## Handoff rule

When your work unblocks another role, set **Action needed** in the Team Log to that role (PM, UX, Dev, or QA).

## Active assignments

Before starting other work, check **Agent assignments** in `docs/TEAM_WORKSPACE.md` Active Work. If you are **Dev**, **UX**, or **QA** and assignments list you, complete those deliverables first and log completion in Team Log.

## Documentation (PM-owned)

The **PM agent** maintains requirements and project documentation:

- `docs/README.md` — documentation index
- `docs/TEAM_WORKSPACE.md` — active work and team log
- `docs/DECISIONS.md` — major decisions
- `docs/features/` — feature requirements
- `docs/backlog/` — assessments and deferred work
- `docs/future-enhancements/` — large PRDs not yet scheduled (registry + specs)

**UX and Dev:** Do not restructure docs. Add findings to your feature spec section or request a Team Log entry. PM will formalize assessments and broadcast decisions.

**Major decisions:** PM records in `docs/DECISIONS.md` and announces in Team Log. If you make a scope/architecture choice, leave a Team Log note tagged `Decision:` for PM to capture.
